Pullenspro/
├── api/
│   ├── index.py          # FastAPI backend (Redis · rate limiting · circuit breakers)
│   └── requirements.txt  # Python dependencies
├── pages/
│   ├── bulk.tsx          # CSV upload page with drag-and-drop
│   └── jobs.tsx          # Job monitor with smart polling
├── .env.example          # Environment variable reference
├── railway.json          # Railway deployment config
└── README.md
Features
Backend (api/index.py)
Sliding-window rate limiting per IP via Redis sorted sets
Per-service circuit breakers (Hunter / Clearbit / Apollo) with CLOSED → OPEN → HALF_OPEN FSM
Redis result caching (1h TTL, cache-key based on lead fields)
Bulk CSV processing up to 5,000 rows with bounded asyncio.Semaphore concurrency
Streaming CSV download of enriched results
Webhook notification on job completion
/health, /circuit-breakers, /cache/stats observability endpoints
Frontend
pages/bulk.tsx — drag-and-drop CSV upload, source toggles, concurrency slider, XHR upload progress
pages/jobs.tsx — real-time job cards, smart polling (1.5s active / 30s idle), filter/search, cancel + CSV download
Quick Start
# Backend
cd api
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn index:app --reload

# Frontend (add pages/ to an existing Next.js project)
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000 next dev
CSV Format
